The death toll of the massive car crash that took place in the Impendle area, just outside Boston, has risen to four. On Sunday, Midlands EMS paramedics responded to the a crash where bakkie had rolled, carrying soccer players returning from a match in the Impendle area. According to Midlands EMS spokesperson Roland Robertson, when the accident happened, there was one soccer player who was declared dead on the scene and four others who were critical. “There were multiple critical patients requiring urgent advanced life support care with four of them being placed on manual ventilators on the scene,” said Robertson. He also added that about 10 other people needed medical attention and were treated on the scene. The uMgungundlovu District Sport Confederation on Tuesday released a statement expressing its shock and sadness following the death of the players. “This tragic accident has robbed us of young talented soccer stars of Swamp United from Impendle Municipality. On the 28th of March, we received news that three players had passed away and now we have just heard that another has also passed away today,” read the  confederation’s statement.